parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to lock up or become loose, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel pulls to the left or right
the steering wheel becomes loose
the vehicle veers to one side
the steering wheel locks up
the EPS warning light illuminates
and the vehicle's stability control and traction control systems may be affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the vehicle to shudder or vibrate while driving, leading to loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Shuddering or vibrating while driving
usually between 25-50 mph
loss of power
hesitation when accelerating
and rough ride.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or hesitation can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission slipping or hesitation
loss of power
hesitation when accelerating
and rough ride.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake failure can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake failure
sudden acceleration
and loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The shifter or transmission malfunction can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Shifter or transmission malfunction
sudden acceleration
and loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, leading to a loss of braking power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal makes a loud grinding or clanking noise
the brake warning light stays lit
the "Check Brake System" message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal makes a loud grinding or clanking noise
the brake warning light stays lit
the "Check Brake System" message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle slides or fails to stop when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, leading to a loss of braking power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal makes a loud grinding or clanking noise
the brake warning light stays lit
the "Check Brake System" message appears on the dashboard.
